		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Wondrous Item - Very Rare (Requires Attunement)</em></p><p><strong>Buff</strong></p><ul><li><p>The helm is set with [[/r 1d10 # Diamonds]] diamonds, [[/r 2d10 # Rubies]] rubies, [[/r 3d10 # Fire Opals]] fire opals, and [[/r 4d10 # Opals]] opals. Any gem pried from the helm crumbles to dust. If all gems are removed or destroyed, the helm loses its magic.</p></li><li><p><strong>Diamond Light.</strong> While at least one diamond remains, the helm emits a 30-foot Emanation. If an Undead is within the area, it is filled with Dim Light and any Undead that starts its turn there takes 1d6 Radiant damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ruby Resistance.</strong> While at least one ruby remains, you have Resistance to Fire damage.</p></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Action</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Fire Opal Flames.</strong> While at least one fire opal remains, you can cause a weapon you are holding to burst into flame. The flames shed Bright Light in a 10-foot radius and Dim Light for an additional 10 feet, are harmless to you, and cause the weapon to deal an extra 1d6 Fire damage on a hit. The flames last until you take a Bonus Action to extinguish them or until you drop or stow the weapon.</p></li><li><p><strong>Spell Casting.</strong> Expend one of the helm's gems to cast a spell (save DC 18). The gem is destroyed when used.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Opal:</strong> <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.jdFMmZrR5TJegYvD]{Daylight}</em></p></li><li><p><strong>Fire Opal:</strong> <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.pbT9cw6nsjpmwrVZ]{Fireball}</em></p></li><li><p><strong>Diamond:</strong> <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.MZIcL4XW7JTm2fjn]{Prismatic Spray}</em></p></li><li><p><strong>Ruby:</strong> <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.zQ7lBRzId8peTjor]{Wall of Fire}</em></p></li></ul></li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Utility</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Taking Fire Damage.</strong> If you are wearing the helm and take Fire damage as a result of failing a spell's saving throw, roll [[/r 1d20]]. On a 1, the helm emits beams of light from its remaining gems and is destroyed. Each creature in a 60-foot Emanation originating from you must succeed on a [[/save DEX 17]]{DC 17 Dexterity saving throw} or take Radiant damage equal to the number of gems remaining in the helm.</p></li><li><p><strong>Tracking Gems.</strong> Keep a tally of the remaining Diamonds, Rubies, Fire Opals, and Opals to know which benefits are active.</p></li></ul><section><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>Use the description fields above to note the count of each gem. If you roll a 1 for <strong>Taking Fire Damage</strong>, the <strong>Explosive Emanation</strong> activity will prompt for the number of remaining gems and handle the damage automatically.</p></section>",
